{{/*
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  WHAT  : files inside the chezmoi source tree that should NOT be applied
          to the target ($HOME).
  WHERE : home/.chezmoiignore  (one of chezmoi's special source files)
  WHY   :
    * .gitkeep stubs only exist so empty leaf dirs survive in git; they
      must never land in $HOME.
    * The defensive entries (README.md, LICENSE, ...) cover the case where
      someone drops one of those files inside home/ by mistake — chezmoi's
      source dir is `home/`, so anything at the *repo* root is naturally
      out of scope already.
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*/ -}}

# Empty-dir markers — kept in git, never apply to $HOME.
**/.gitkeep

# Defensive: anything below would leak documentation/build cruft into $HOME
# if it ever ended up inside home/.
README.md
README.*
LICENSE
LICENSE.*
PLAN.md
docs
scripts
